            <div type="translation">
                <p>Κύριε βοήθει τῷ σῷ δούλῳ Ἰωάννῃ πρωτοσπαθαρίῳ ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου / κριτῇ τοῦ βήλου καὶ γηροτρόφῳ τῷ Χρυσοβέργῃ.</p>
                <p xml:lang="en">Lord, help your servant John Chrysoberges <hi rend="italic">protospatharios</hi>, <hi rend="italic">epi tou Chrysotriklinou</hi>, / <hi rend="italic">krites</hi> of the Velon, and <hi rend="italic">gerotrophos</hi>.</p>
                <p xml:lang="de">Herr, hilf deinem Diener Johannes Chrysoberges <hi rend="italic">protospatharios</hi>, <hi rend="italic">epi tou Chrysotriklinou</hi>, / <hi rend="italic">krites</hi> des Velon und <hi rend="italic">gerotrophos</hi>.</p>
              </div>
            <div type="commentary" subtype="text">
                <p>The owner of the seal, John Chrysoberges, is known from sigillographic evidence, and his career can be reconstructed in the wake of the most recent findings.[1] Two previous stages of his career can be inferred from two seals, kept in the Archaeological Museum in Istanbul and at Dumbarton Oaks, where he is attested as βασιλικὸς σπαθαροκανδιδάτος[2] and as σπαθαροκανδιδάτος, πρωτοκαγκελλάριος τοῦ γενικοῦ, κριτής, ἀναγραφεύς and κουράτωρ Μελιτηνῆς respectively.[3] Our specimen shows him at the highest stage of his hitherto known career as προτοσπαθάριος, ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου, κριτὴς τοῦ βήλου and γηροτρόφος. This means that John Chrysoberges cumulates his high dignities and offices with that of γηροτρόφος, i.e. director of a γηροτροφεῖον (or γηροκομεῖον), a home for the destitute elderly set within the context of the charitable foundations (εὐαγεῖς οἶκοι).[4]</p>
              </div>
            <div type="commentary" subtype="footnotes">
                  <p xml:id="footnote-1">
                      <!--PMBZ-Link okay?-->
                      [1]. See <bibl><ptr target="PBW"/>, <citedRange unit="entry"><ref target="http://pbw2016.kdl.kcl.ac.uk/person/Ioannes/20484/">Ioannes no. 20484</ref></citedRange></bibl> = <bibl><ptr target="PmbZOnline"/>, <citedRange unit="entry"><ref target="https://www.degruyter.com/database/PMBZ/entry/PMBZ25534/html">no. 23380</ref></citedRange></bibl>. The reading of the legend of the seal mentioned in <bibl><ptr target="PBW"/>, <citedRange unit="entry"><ref target="http://pbw2016.kdl.kcl.ac.uk/boulloterion/3683/">Boulloterion no. 3683</ref></citedRange></bibl>, Κύριε βοήθει τῷ σῷ δούλῳ Ἰωάννῃ πρωτοσπαθαρίῳ ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου κριτῇ τοῦ βήλου γηροτρόφῳ τῷ Χρυσοβέργῃ τῷ Νικερίτῃ is evidently incorrect; τῷ Νικερίτῃ was mistakenly added and ought to be expunged.
                  </p>
                  <p xml:id="footnote-2">
                      [2]. <bibl><ptr target="Istanbul"/>, <citedRange unit="page">p. 510, no. 5.223</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                  <p xml:id="footnote-3">
                      <bibl><ptr target="DOsealsOnline"/>, <citedRange unit="entry"><ref target="https://www.doaks.org/resources/seals/byzantine-seals/BZS.1947.2.1066/view">BZS.1947.2.1066</ref></citedRange></bibl>
                      [3]. Dumbarton Oaks BZS.1947.2.1066 (Shaw Collection), published in <bibl><ptr target="DOseals4"/>, <citedRange unit="page">p. 159, no. 68.6</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                <p xml:id="footnote-4">
                    [4]. On the office of the γηροτρόφος (or γηροκόμος), see <bibl><ptr target="Leontaritou1996"/>, especially <citedRange unit="page">p. 134-140</citedRange></bibl>. On the administration of the house for the elderly, see <bibl><ptr target="Constantelos1991"/>, especially <citedRange unit="page">p. 222-240</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="Talbot1984"/>, <citedRange unit="page">especially p. 275-278</citedRange></bibl>. For a broad analysis of the administration of the charitable foundations in Byzantium, see <bibl><ptr target="Kaplan1976"/></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="Kaplan2006"/></bibl>, as well as <bibl><ptr target="Kaplan2006a"/></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="Volk1983"/></bibl>. The office of the γηροκόμος will be object of an in-depth investigation carried out by M. Filosa in her doctoral thesis focussing on the administration of the charitable foundations in the light of lead seals.
                </p>
              </div>
